
Array.rb: 

    This micro benchmark is used to compare the performance difference between with and without monitoring.

    To disable array monitoring, insert the following code in rubybop/ruby/array.c to disable tracking:
         promise_ary_elm(VALUE ary, int idx){
            --> return;
            ...
         }
         use_ary_elm(VALUE ary, int idx){
            --> return;
            ...
         }
         promise_ary(VALUE ary){
            --> return;
            ...
         }
         use_ary(VALUE ary){
            --> return;
            ...
         }
         use_promise_ary(VALUE ary) {
            -->return;
            ...
         }

instanceVariable.rb:

    This mirco benchmark is used to compare the performance difference between with and without monitoring.

    To disable instance variable monitoring, the following code in rubybop/ruby/variable.c should be commented out:

    val_getter(ID id, void *data, struct global_variable *var) {

 -->   // BOP_record_read(var, sizeof(struct global_variable));

    }

    val_setter(VALUE val, ID id, void *data, struct global_variable *var) {

 -->   // BOP_record_write(var, sizeof(struct global_variable));
    
    }

ppr.rb:

    This file is used to profile the overhead of creating PPR tasks



